    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-01T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-01T14:00:00-05:00" n="122"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-01T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 1, 1951—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 468. For Hickerson <gloss
                        target="#t_UNA1">UNA</gloss>, and Ingram, <gloss target="#t_UNI1"
                        >UNI</gloss>, from Hall. Re contributions scale. Ref telecon. Package deal
                    for consideration follows: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>US propose adoption Contributions Committee report with reduction US
                            contribution to 33-⅓ percent and secretariat distribution amount of
                            reduction across all other members on basis assessments recommended by
                            Contributions Committee.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Resolve to distribute surplus of $1,230,000 for 1950 to membership
                            rather than transferring it to <gloss target="#t_WCF1"
                            >WCF</gloss>.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Call upon all members to endeavor pay ½ their annual contributions on
                            January 1 and balance by July 1 of each year.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>US propose that reduction to 33-⅓ percent of advance to <gloss
                                target="#t_WCF1">WCF</gloss> of member having highest contribution
                            rate should take place only after members contributing at least ⅓ of
                            cost of budget, i.e., US or a group equalling ⅓ have indicated ability
                            contribute ½ of their contribution early in fiscal years.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Vorys suggests in addition US should offer to prove this question matter of
                    principle of offering $1,500,000, conditional to <gloss target="#t_TA1"
                        >TA</gloss> if contribution percentage reduced.</p>
                <p>This would involve following Congressional action: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>1. Approval 18 months appropriation for next fiscal year for <gloss
                                target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Authorization of additional $1,500,000 from <gloss target="#t_TA1"
                                >TA</gloss> program for multilateral programs. This could be done by
                            amendment authorization provision and administrative transfer from
                            bilateral to multilateral channels.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Arithmetical calculations cannot be completed here and may require variations in
                    proposal. Could you, after mathematical analysis <pb facs="0218" n="196"
                        xml:id="pg_196"/> on basis $40,000,000 dollar assessment budget, send
                    comments and any suggestion for modifications.</p>
                <p>Early preliminary reactions Staats<note n="1" xml:id="d122fn1">Elmer B. Staats,
                        Assistant Director, Bureau of the Budget.</note> or Rice<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d122fn2">Stuart A. Rice, Assistant Director for Statistical
                        Standards, Bureau of the Budget. Rice was U.S. member on the United Nations
                        Committee on Contributions.</note> for Budget Bureau and <gloss
                        target="#t_TCA1">TCA</gloss> on acceptability Vorys proposal would be
                    helpful.</p>
                <p>Possible variation above would be to get secretariat to introduce all above
                    points except <gloss target="#t_TA1">TA</gloss> contribution and delegation
                    could then support. [Hall.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
